                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2981a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3839. Press is publishing report from London that Great Britain has issued
                    instructions practically closing Scandinavia and the Netherlands to American
                    commerce. Investigate and report what is the nature of the new restrictions, if
                    any, that apparently give rise to this report. Also, if such action has been
                    taken or appears to be contemplated, ascertain if possible what relation may
                    exist between this and retaliatory legislation by recent Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
